Jeanette Chabalala, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Three men sustained burns and &ldquo;traumatic&rdquo; injuries when their light aircraft made an emergency landing at Lanseria Airport on Tuesday, paramedics said. It burst into flames shortly after landing at 15:30, Netcare 911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said.Paramedics treated two of the men on scene before taking them to a level 1 trauma burn facility in Johannesburg.Paramedics from another company treated the third man and took him to hospital.The aircraft, registration ZU-TVB appears to be a converted Cessna 402 Falcon.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.